== Etymology ==
From Latin ''[[indulgere]]'' meaning to give free reign to, [[complaisant]]

== Verb ==

=== Intransitive ===
#(often followed by in) take pleasure in
#:''He looked at the chocolate but didn't indulge''

=== Transitive ===
#satisfy the wishes of
#:''Gary indulged them with money''
#give in to

